commit.message:
Remove unnecessary entries with -text attribute

The first entry '* text=auto !eol' is enough to make sure all text files
are correctly handling CRLF when cloning and pushing in Windows.
In fact entries with '-text' attribute remove the necessary conversion
and can therefore cause files with CRLF to be wrongly committed.
